The initial case was suspended earlier this year, after Judge Mandela Makaula recused himself. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Pastor Timothy Omotoso’s rape and human trafficking retrial has been postponed until Wednesday. The initial case was suspended earlier this year after Judge Mandela Makaula recused himself. READ: Timothy Omotoso retrial begins This after it emerged his wife had business interests at a guesthouse where some state witnesses were staying. On Tuesday, Omotoso's defence lawyer Peter Daubermann asked for more information relating to the charges. Omotoso remains in custody while his two co-accused Lusanda Sulani and Zukiswa Sitho are out on bail.